HEADWORD: Wapatoo
<hw>Wap"a*too`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The edible tuber of a species of arrowhead (<spn>Sagittaria
variabilis</spn>); -- so called by the Indians of Oregon.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>wappato</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

